### What this means

{% if drift_type == 'covariate' %}
Input feature distributions have shifted. The model's learned relationship
P(Y|X) may still be valid, but the model is now receiving inputs that differ
from its training distribution. Monitor evaluation accuracy closely.
{% elif drift_type == 'label' %}
The output / ground-truth distribution P(Y) has shifted. The target concept
may have evolved. The model's predictions may no longer align with
current business reality.
{% elif drift_type == 'concept' %}
The relationship between inputs and outputs P(Y|X) has changed without
a detectable input shift. This is the hardest drift type to remediate —
a retrain with recent labelled data is typically required.
{% elif drift_type == 'data_quality' %}
The signal is consistent with an upstream data pipeline defect rather than
genuine distributional drift. A retrain will NOT fix this — the data
pipeline must be investigated first.
{% endif %}

